    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A short sequence of bits (binary digits) that can be operated on as a unit by a computer; the smallest usable machine word."
        entry
          definition "(most commonly) A unit of computing storage equal to eight bits, which can represent any of 256 distinct values."
          example "The word “hello” fits into five bytes of ASCII code."
          synonyms (B octet)
